Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia, Fabricato Rise; BVC Falls

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-17T14:56:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/colombian-stocks-bancolombia-fabricato-rise-bvc-falls.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:38 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index was little changed at 14,031.29, while the
Colcap Index advanced 0.1 percent to 1,702.37.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , Colombia’s biggest bank, rose
0.5 percent to 29,240 pesos after it was raised to “hold” from
“sell” yesterday by Interbolsa SA. Interbolsa raised its year-
end target price 26 percent to 32,550 pesos on the outlook for
loan growth,  interest rates  and borrowers’ creditworthiness,
according to an e-mailed statement from Colombia’s biggest
brokerage.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the operator of
Colombia’s main stock exchange, fell 0.2 percent to 41.6 pesos
after its shareholders decided yesterday to postpone a vote on a
planned merger with Peru’s bourse following the election of
Peruvian President-elect Ollanta Humala.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s largest textile maker,
gained 3.4 percent to 61.5 pesos after White House Chief of
Staff  William Daley  said yesterday a consensus has emerged in
Congress for renewing aid for workers who lose jobs to global
competition and passing free-trade agreements before the August
recess.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
